    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's hard to see how long-term stability helps a small shop that might go under next year because of the upfront costs though. do you think the benefit of avoiding \"future costs\" is actually a realistic economic factor for these smaller guys, or is it more of an idealistic argument used to justify the mandates?",
